properties.description: Teotihuacn reaches a population of 60,000 to 80,000
The Imperial Roman army reaches 300,000 soldiers
Timgad (Thamugas), a Roman colonial town in North Africa, is founded by Roman Emperor Trajan
properties.source: LeGlay, Marcel; Voisin, Jean-Louis; Le Bohec, Yann (2001). A History of Rome (Second ed.). Malden, Massachusetts: Blackwell. p. 271. ISBN 0-631-21858-0.

properties.description: Emperor Trajan and Frontinus become Roman consuls.
Pacores (last well-documented king of the Indo-Parthian kingdom) takes the throne.
The Hopewell tradition roughly begins in what is now Ohio.
In China, the wheelbarrow makes its first appearance.
